text.__SUMMARY__: Tropidolaemus laticinctus is a species of venomous snake in the pit viper subfamily, Crotalinae. Its common names are broad-banded temple pitviper, or broad-banded pit viper. It is endemic to the Indonesian island of Sulawesi.
text.Description:
Unlike other temple viper species, this species lacks age-related and sexually dimorphic coloration.
